GT_Text.Value: ABSTRACT Turkeys from a randombred control line (RBC2) and its subline (F) selected for increased 16-wk BW were tested for primary and secondary antibody re-sponses to SRBC antigen (BA). Previous studies have shown that the F line was more susceptible to Pasteurella multocida and Newcastle disease virus than was the RBC2 line. Individuals from the RBC2 and F lines were intravenously injected with 1mL 5% SRBC antigen or 0.1 mL undiluted BA at 4 and 6 wk of age; blood samples were collected at 0, 4, 7, and 10 d post-immunization. Total, IgG, and IgM titers were measured by agglutination assays.
